Governor Nasir El-Rufai of Kaduna State yesterday assured foreign observers on election monitoring duty in the state of adequate security. The governor met with foreign observers from the International Republican Institute, of the United States, in his office. The observers had in the meeting sought clarification on his comments on a recent live television programme, which sparked controversy. Governor El-Rufai urged people of the state to come out and vote for the party, and candidates of their choice.  Northern youths chide El-Rufai over comment on foreigners observers CSOs protest at US Embassy over El-Rufai’s ‘body-bag’ comment Presidency backs El-Rufa’i, says 'he spoke in defense of national interest'